title: Northeast Investigator Shoal
text:
Northeast Investigator Shoal, also known as Dalagang Bukid Shoal (); <a href="Mandarin%20Chinese">Mandarin</a> ; , also marked as Investigator Northeast Shoal on some nautical charts, is a <a href="shoal">shoal</a> in the <a href="Spratly%20Islands">Spratly group of islands</a> in <a href="South%20China%20sea">South China sea</a>.
The submerged coral <a href="atoll">atoll</a> is located 32 nautical miles from at 9° 10' N, 116° 28' E. A small feature with an area of just 2 square kilometres, the shoal has a few rocks at the western edge that are just about visible at high water.
